"3","# Aphelopus nigriceps: iso. Olmi: 1999

## Provisional Red List status: DD
- A2bc
- A3b
- D2

## Red List Justification
*N/A*

### Narrative
This dryinid wasp acts as a parasitoid/predator on Typhloybinae, Cicadellidae (Leafhopper). A recorded host in Britain is Eurhadina concinna (Germar). Sparsely recorded from Hampshire to Kent and north to Lancashire and Co, Durham in England and also known from Scotland (Dumfries & Galloway, Highlands).

Insufficient data were available to reach a supportable conclusion on the threat status for this taxon.

