"6","# Aphelopus atratus: iso. Olmi: 1994

## Provisional Red List status: DD
- A2bc
- A3b
- D2

## Red List Justification
*N/A*

### Narrative
Also known as A. holommelas Richards, 1939 in Perkins (1976). Records of this dryinid wasp are from Devon to Kent and north to Cheshire and Co. Durham, Wales (Glamorgan, Pembrokeshire) and Scotland (Dumfries and Galloway, Lanarkshire, Edinburgh, Lothian, Angus, Highlands) which is almost certainly a true reflection of it's distribution. It acts as a parasitoid/predator on Typhloybinae,Cicadellidae (Leaf Hoppers) and has been reared from Lebra albastriella (Fallén), A. wahlbergi (Boheman), Eupteryx aurata Linnaeus), E. cyclops Matsumura, E. melissae (Curtis), E. urticae (Fabricius), E.hippocast (Edwards), Fagocyha cruenta (Herrich-Schäffer), Ribautiana tenerrima (Herrich-Schäffer), R. ulmi )Linnaeus) and also recorded on Typhlocyba opaca on apple.

Insufficient data were available to reach a supportable conclusion on the threat status for this taxon.

