## Provisional Red List status: DD
- A2bc
- A3b
- D2

## Red List Justification
*N/A*

### Narrative
Records of the wasp - the largest of it's genus in GB - are restricted to the south coast of the Isle of Wight, where it was first recorded in 1950. Despite being present over a long period, there is too little data to be confident in details of ecology and biology which would allow targeted surveying to confirm the stated distribution.

Insufficient data were available to reach a supportable conclusion on the threat status for this taxon.

