"60","# Andrena tridentata: iso. Perkins: 1919

## Provisional Red List status: RE
- A2

## Red List Justification
*N/A*

### Narrative
This has always been a very rare bee in the UK and some of the most related species are also generally uncommon. There have been difficulties in identification / verification of some older records – the confirmed records are restricted to 9 locations in Suffolk and Dorset, with the last record being in Dorset (Norden, near Corfe Castle) in 1944. It is localised and scarce in Europe and is evaluated as RE in GB.



