"168","# Cardiocondyla britteni: iso. Bolton: 2019

## Provisional Red List status: NE


## Red List Justification
*N/A*

### Narrative
This species of ant has been recorded only once. According to Crawley (1920) “The type locality is West Didsbury to where it has apparently been imported via the Liverpool harbour with “Butter Beans”. There is doubt over the identification of the species and the genus is restricted to India and the Oriental region. As such it is a historic synanthropic colonist and has not been evaluated.



