"212","# Eucera nigrescens: iso. Amiet et al: 2007

## Provisional Red List status: RE
- A2

## Red List Justification
*N/A*

### Narrative
Historically this species was mostly restricted the southeast of England and more so in the twentieth century (East Sussex and Kent). The most recent records were Kent in 1966 (Pluckley) and 1970 (Maplesden). This genus of bees (with notably long antennae) is very distinctive, the species was always scarce, and with no further records, despite targeted surveying in the assessment period, it is evaluated as RE.



