"224","# Halictus maculatus: iso. Amiet et al: 2001

## Provisional Red List status: RE
- A2

## Red List Justification
*N/A*

### Narrative
There are some 19th century records of this distinctive halictid bee, and two thriving nesting aggregations survived in South Devon (Chudleigh) from 1919-1930, but there have been no more recent records and RE is an appropriate evaluation.



