"252","# Megachile lapponica: iso. Perkins: 1925

## Provisional Red List status: NE


## Red List Justification
One record from 1847. Considered to be of very dubious presence in GB.

### Narrative
Somewhat curiously, the only record of this species in 1847 was - as with M. ericetorum – from Weybridge in Surrey. With no records before or since it must be strongly suspected as a synanthropic colonist and is not evaluated.



