### Narrative
This mound building “wood ant” has strong populations on the Channel Islands (out with the geographical scope of this assessment). It is worth noting the taxonomic and identification difficulties associated with the “wood ants” historically and the species been subject to targeted survey effort without being found. Mainland records were only made from two locations – from the Dorset heathland near Wareham and the Bournemouth area where it was discovered in 1864. The last known nest, near Wareham, died out in 1987 leading to an evaluation of RE.



### Quantified Attributes
|Attribute|Result|
|---|---|
|Synanthropy|No|
|Vagrancy|No|
|Colonisation|No|
|Nomenclature|No|


## National Rarity
Nationally Extinct (*EX*)



