"527","# Dinetus pictus: iso. Richards: 1980

## Provisional Red List status: NE


## Red List Justification
Only known GB record from 1950 is highly dubious.

### Narrative
Old records come from observations noted by F. Smith prior to 1880 around Windsor and Ascot in Berkshire (Falk, 1991). A more recent record is from Oxshott Heath, Surrey, in 1950 (Baker in Baldock, 2010) has not been inspected and there is doubt about the identification. All records (including from 1950 – if correct) are regarded as vagrants and therefore the species is not evaluated.



