Seen in 1853, then again in ~2022 with a verified presence in London. Not found during re-search, likely synanthropic.

### Narrative
This wasp was recorded in 1853 (Weybridge, Surrey) and not seen again until 2022 (London – A. Madgwick – 1 male). An aerial, wood nesting species, it is regarded as a synanthropic colonist and is therefore not evaluated.



### Quantified Attributes
|Attribute|Result|
|---|---|
|Synanthropy|Synanthropic Colonist|
|Vagrancy|No|
|Colonisation|No|
|Nomenclature|No|






